Three suspects have been arrested in an early morning violence which erupted in Ilorin, Kwara State capital, on Tuesday. Another suspect seriously injured in the violence has been admitted at an undisclosed hospital in Ilorin. The violence erupted at about 0600hours at Adeta, Isale, Jagun and Kuntu areas of the state capital. Dangerous weapons such as guns, bottles and machetes were freely used by hoodlums of the areas who engaged themselves in the bloody clash. DAILY POST could not ascertain the cause of the violence at the time of this report but no casualty was recorded. Imagemaker of the Kwara State Police Command, Okasanmi Ajayi, who confirmed the incident on Tuesday, said the “command recieved a disturbing information of the unruly behavior of some youths of Adeta , Isale Jagun and Kuntu areas of Adewole today at about 0600hrs.” He said the Commissioner of Police, Tuesday Assayomo, on the receipt of the information quickly dispatched a detachment of policemen to the area to restore peace and arrest the perpetrators of the near breakdown of law and order in the area. Okasanmi said investigation on the matter is ongoing to unravel the remote and immediate cause(s) of the crisis that led to damage to some vehicles parked on the affected streets. The state police commissioner has also ordered the state CID to take over the case for a discreet investigation. He advised parents/guardians to warn their children to eschew violence and make use of laid down channels to air their grievances if any, rather than taking the laws into their hands. Assayomo further warned that anybody arrested in connection with this crisis and any other one for that matter would be made to face the full wrath of the law. Meanwhile, calm has been restored in the area, with security operatives urging members of the public to go about their lawful businesses as policemen have been stationed at the affected areas to ensure no further breach to the peace in the areas.